iation of rhythms outside normal limits, or appearance of new rhythms where none existed previously, are associated with disease. One of the most interesting features of the book is that it makes a start at explaining "dynamical diseases" that are not the result of infection by pathogens but that stem from abnormalities in the timing of essential functions. From Clocks to Chaos provides a firm foundation for understanding dynamic processes in physiology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBiological rhythmsxMathematics. 0aBiological rhythms. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Biology.2bisacsh  aAV block.  aCantor function.  aGABA receptors.  aHodgkin-Huxley equations.  aLiapunov number.  aParkinsonian tremor.  aaccessory pathways.  aalternans.  abistability.  ablood vessel rhythms.  acardiac rhythm.  acircle map.  adepolarization.  adifferential equations.  adynamical diseases.  aelectrocardiogram.  aequilibrium points.  afibrillation.  afictive locomotion.  agraphical iteration.  ahyperventilation.  ainsulin administration.  alamprey locomotion.  amechanical ventilation.  amutual inhibition.  aneuromuscular junction.  aorganizing centers.  aquadratic map.  arefractory period.  asequential disinhibition.  atachycardia.  avagus nerve.1 aMackey, Michael C., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691221793zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691221793423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691221793.jpg  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  a